## Description
The **Extract Documents (DA-hotspot) **task allows to extract documents from the Digital Archiving 3 software service using the legacy Digital Archiving Endpoint configuration.

> Important

This is a legacy task created to support the migration to Digital Archiving 3 build 3.37 (January 2023 release). For all new applications, please refer to the latest version of the task: [Extract Documents (DA) Batch Workflow Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/extract-documents-da-batch-workflow-task-reference).

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Store &gt; Resource **field and select the Digital Archiving Hotspot resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see: [Digital Archiving Hotspot Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-hotspot-resource-reference).

- Enter the required **Input **parameters:

**Field**

**Description**

**Index pattern**

Name of the XML index file or a filename pattern (in glob format) to identify it (for example, *input.xml *or **.xml*).

> Important

If multiple files or no files match the index pattern, the task will fail.

**Query element**

Path to the XML tag containing the data to extract (for example: */FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/DA*)

**Category attribute**

Name of the input attribute containing the value of the requested document class (for example, *documentCategory*)

- Select the required **Output &gt; Content**; the possible values are:

**Metadata**: The payload is an XML file describing the metadata of the documents returned.

- **Metadata with embedded documents**: The payload is an XML file with the metadata and an additional tag containing the embedded documents embedded in Base64 format.

- **Metadata and documents**: The payload is a ZIP file containing the metadata XML file and the documents as separate files.

- **Documents**: The payload is the document (in case of single document returned), or a ZIP file containing one or more documents.

- *(optional) *If you selected **Metadata **or **Metadata with embedded documents**, select the **Unique metadata filename **option to add a unique designator to the metadata filename; for example:

`output.xml &gt; output_{designator}.xml`
> Note

For more information on the structure of the DA3 Extractor's input and output, see: [Digital Archiving 3 Extractor Input and Output Structure](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-3-extractor-input-and-output-structure).
